<br>
We have people ask us all the time what does FCAV do. This is a very fair question, and I hope to explain clearly.<br>
<br>
Most would agree that &quot;Traditional American Values&quot; are &quot;Conservative Values&quot;, so leading our country back to traditional values is our overall goal. On a personal note, I am doing this for my 10 year old Grandaughter. It would be a tragedy to have her grow up in a Socialist regime, so the following is how FCAV wants to keep this from happening.<br>
<br>
Getting back to traditional values has a lot to do with politics. If we can keep electing Conservative leaders we can almost gaurantee a swing back to these values. This raises the question as to &quot;how&quot; we affect voting in the future. This is where FCAV wants to be effective. We will not endorse a candidate or a party (as a non-profit we cannot), but we can help show folks how the Conservative ideology is best for our country.<br>
<br>
One way to do this is by education. This means going after our future voters and showing them the way. FCAV has 2 groups that we want to reach out to. First is the &quot;Future Voter&quot;, we do this by getting into the schools in any way possible. From endorsing the promotion of more Conservative Teachers being hired in the Public Schools to actually having personal contact with students. FCAV is about to sponsor our very first Essay Contest for High School Seniors. The &quot;Subject&quot; the students have to write about is &quot;Why traditional Values are important to me&quot;. Of course there will be prizes given out, but most importantly, we get students across the country actually thinking about the subject. This is part of our &quot;personal contact&quot;. There are numerous variations of this we can use, including the one I personnally like... giving out Scholarships to Conservative Universities.<br>
<br>
The second group that FCAV wants to reach out to is what the Libs like to call &quot;The Disenfranchised&quot;. We can accomplish this, but it will take an enormous amount of Money and elbow grease. FCAV would like to start-up a Free Newspaper! One that has paid advertising in it, but more importantly, it contains Conservative articles, opinions, facts, statistics, and even comics. We target this group by providing this paper for Free, and by selective distribution. One idea is to put the Free paper in convenience stores in low income areas. These folks usually get their news from TV and Newspapers, mostly because they cannot afford a PC or the Internet. It's time we showed them the lies the have been fed by those that only wanted their vote, and never had any intentions of really helping them. <br>
<br>
Ok, I promised to keep this short, so I will.<br>
<br>
The above explanations are very short and only scratch the surface of what we as an Organization want to acheive. All comments and ideas are welcome.<br>
<br>
David Swanson<br>
